        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "There are a couple of places that Zend_Db_Adapter_Mysqli checks for a connection.  Why do these checks not utilize mysqli_ping?\r\n\r\nI am running into instances where I am getting a \"MySQL Server has gone away\" error, and I believe if we used mysqli_ping in the two places I've pointed out in the patch file, you would have a better chance of not getting that error message."
        },
